Problem Statement :
  Target Profile/User:
      Balan(22 years old)
  Problem           : He have a amount of Rupees 5000 and eager in investing.But the core problem is the fear of lossing the money 
                      due to inadequate knowledge in investing and low confidence in assurance of his money
  Traditional Cases:  In more of the FinTech Applications, the first time users got frustrated due high cognitive load and 
                      feels discomfort in the investement due to low konwlegdge in trading or investing money.They simply 
                      opens the application and visualizing the stocks.He doesn't  even know what stock should he want to use 
                      to grow the money and how should be the process and random investing takes place and the outcome becomes 
                      loss or user frustration and leave the application.The main problem is he had the interst and splending money
                      on investing but he doesn't know the flow
Scope and Solution:   To solve this we made  a application rather than the traditional application.FirstStep Invest shifts the focus from 
                      transaction mechanics (buying/selling) to risk transparency. The prototype scaffolds a low-friction, 5-screen guided
                      journey that balances potential gains with highly visible, equal-weighted potential losses. By breaking down jargon into inline, bite-sized contextual definitions,
                      it eliminates cognitive overload and builds structural confidence, allowing the user to complete their first simulated investment decision with total clarity.
  
        
